    <bioghist id="aspace_c3e0d42aff0951b4a746c83fbd9a2b01">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>George Leonidas Lyon, a native of Durham, N.C. and grandson of Washington Duke, was a world
        champion marksman. He coached the United States Trapshooting team to both team and
        individual gold medals in the Games of the V Olympiad held in Stockholm, Sweden in 1912.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_80eee55ed2bd45a9af1c80929732b63b">
      <head>Collection Overview</head>
      <p>The collection includes correspondence, clippings, and photographs. Subjects include Lyon's
        involvement in the sport of trapshooting and Lyon's illness and subsequent death from
        tuberculosis. Photographs include several generations of the related Carr, Duke, Lyon,
        McClamroch, and Watts families.</p>
    </scopecontent>
